{"id":137631,"global_id":"Z2lkOi8vaGFja2Vyb25lL1JlcG9ydC8xMzc2MzE=","url":"https://hackerone.com/reports/137631","title":"SMTP command injection","state":"Closed","substate":"resolved","readable_substate":"Resolved","created_at":"2016-05-10T19:39:06.912Z","submitted_at":"2016-05-10T19:39:06.912Z","is_member_of_team?":false,"reporter":{"disabled":false,"username":"jeremy","url":"/jeremy","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/003/121/d8d8bc5a99a5229118f3f1064beb83458d1d10d6_original.jpg/43e4513b9104ea0d68c9c096cea374ba8440dde3e027af5465c8771e8839a67c"},"is_me?":false,"cleared":false,"hackerone_triager":false,"hacker_mediation":false},"team":{"id":7724,"url":"https://hackerone.com/ruby","handle":"ruby","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/007/724/bb067434deef370d6a0b16c2cbbc030b57c75e92_original.png/43e4513b9104ea0d68c9c096cea374ba8440dde3e027af5465c8771e8839a67c","medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/007/724/bb067434deef370d6a0b16c2cbbc030b57c75e92_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"permissions":[],"submission_state":"open","default_currency":"usd","awards_miles":false,"offers_bounties":true,"state":"public_mode","only_cleared_hackers":false,"pentest_feature_enabled?":false,"profile":{"name":"Ruby","twitter_handle":"","website":"https://www.ruby-lang.org","about":"A Programmer's Best Friend"}},"has_bounty?":false,"in_validation?":false,"rejected_anc_report_that_can_be_sent_back_to_anc_triagers?":false,"can_view_team":true,"can_view_report":true,"is_external_bug":false,"is_published":false,"is_participant":false,"has_collaborators":false,"stage":4,"public":true,"visibility":"full","cve_ids":[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":false,"disclosed_at":"2016-06-30T07:28:29.785Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2016-06-30T07:28:29.659Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2016-06-23T04:09:31.696Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Net::SMTP is vulnerable to RCPT TO/MAIL FROM injection due to lack of input validation and conformance to the SMTP protocol.\n\nPublicly disclosed already: http://www.mbsd.jp/Whitepaper/smtpi.pdf\n\nPeople are wrongly assigning this to the mail gem (http://rubysec.com/advisories/OSVDB-131677/) and thinking it's fixed, when in fact the underlying vuln remains in Net::SMTP.\n\nDiscussed as an issue with the `mail` library here: https://github.com/rubysec/ruby-advisory-db/issues/215. And mentioned that it's likely an issue with net-smtp not doing input validation, per RFC spec: https://github.com/rubysec/ruby-advisory-db/issues/215#issuecomment-163906956\n\nThe mail gem *should* do input validation too, of course. But its responsibility is creating internet messages, and it would validate addresses against that spec. Its responsibility is not SMTP protocol compliance. Net::SMTP is.\n\nAddressing this in Ruby in a timely manner will help resolve the considerable confusion that's emerged due to the lack of response to a publicly disclosed vulnerability.","weakness":{"id":58,"name":"Command Injection - Generic"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2016-07-23T04:09:31.831Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-164712618.73176876,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":9,"voters":["lukasreschke","eveeez","paulos_","silv3rpoision","paragonie-scott","dyabla","arice","pei","troysucks"],"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"activities":[{"id":963303,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hi Jeremy,\n\nWe have a ticket about this in the private GitHub security repository.  I'm pasting the conversation below.\n\n@unak said:\n\nIMO, Net ::SMTP does not have to validate its inputs always.\nThis means that the library does not have to check whether the sender address is RFC5822 compliant or not.\nBut Net::BufferedIO#writeline may have to check the parameter does not contain CR and LF.\n\nThen @shugo said:\n\n\u003e IMO, Net ::SMTP does not have to validate its inputs always.\n\nAgreed.\n\n\u003e This means that the library does not have to check whether the sender address is RFC5822 compliant or not.\n\nIf Net::SMTP verify input, there's a consideration about source routing lists.\nThey should be rejected according to RFC5321.\n\n\u003e But Net::BufferedIO#writeline may have to check the parameter does not contain CR and LF.\n\nI'm not sure whether it should do.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-05-18T15:45:55.314Z","updated_at":"2016-05-18T15:45:55.314Z","actor":{"username":"tenderlove","cleared":false,"url":"/tenderlove","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/003/318/60d828744b5d16813ecbf975fdc453dc4a933f4f_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"ruby","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":964010,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Agree it's not Net::SMTP's job to validate RFC5822 addresses.\n\nIt is Net::SMTP's job to [validate RFC5321 lines](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5321#section-2.3.8) and follow the [command argument syntax](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5321#section-4.1.2).\n\n\u003e SMTP client implementations **MUST NOT** transmit these characters except when they are intended as line terminators and then **MUST**, as indicated above, transmit them only as a \u003cCRLF\u003e sequence.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-05-18T22:40:12.933Z","updated_at":"2016-05-18T22:40:12.933Z","actor":{"username":"jeremy","cleared":false,"url":"/jeremy","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/003/121/d8d8bc5a99a5229118f3f1064beb83458d1d10d6_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"ruby","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1004104,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hi Jeremy,\n\nI'd like to merge the attached patch as a normal bug fix.\nCould you check it?","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-06-08T03:56:26.615Z","updated_at":"2016-06-08T03:56:26.615Z","actor":{"username":"shugo","cleared":false,"url":"/shugo","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/076/177/c63f990ae1ef62a77c2ff1e5b2db5e4dd3db2557_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"attachments":[{"id":98457,"filename":"smtp-injection.diff","type":"text/x-diff","url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/000/098/457/bbf794e64e560269375367545fbf9180f0f53d96/smtp-injection.diff?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22smtp-injection.diff%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27smtp-injection.diff\u0026response-content-type=text%2Fx-diff\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQTTPJWCNM%2F20211011%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20211011T133950Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjEHUaCXVzLXdlc3QtMiJIMEYCIQDOwM9%2B2Ol25EbTHv2AOl1ZXwoFCdY81Kf4Cj%2BZw5bGagIhALNw4OtUKzuuJ5JDnXIMoizsmzLoA6B3TMlT4JOm5OV%2FKoMECO7%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2FwEQAhoMMDEzNjE5Mjc0ODQ5IgxBja9Y5H4vqpYK%2BZIq1wMKEFztYF934tg2oiDnz06aS%2BIxaoyblb3k6%2F%2BxBMgQzBtDrU0ocKh0rsBsPTyultSX957Ztb0Xxm%2BlSHqRsjq6d7mkuWsgkJaqQC34P%2FPoowX%2BlH2ZrTK%2FmkJH0GzYv